<div class="row">
	<div class="col-md-12">
		<h3>
			The Rules
		</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Miles completed must be submitted to Carol (in the UK) and Dominica (in Poland) each Friday, the miles will then be entered onto the tracking site.</li>
			<li>We ask that each individual or team looks to gain sponsorship for their efforts – there is no minimum or maximum requirement but we do ask that the individuals and teams do make the effort to gain as much external sponsorship as they can.</li>
			<li>We will set-up a Just Giving Page for donations to be made and also provide sponsorship forms to do it the old fashioned way.</li>
			<li>Each individual will be responsible themselves for gaining sponsorship and in-turn, collecting their own money.</li>
			<li>There will be monthly prizes for whoever does the most miles in that month.</li>
			<li>We will also provide a prize for the team and individual that accumulates the highest amount of sponsorship.</li>
			<li>If non-cycling members of IT want to do other activities around this activity outside of work to attract sponsorship we will be more than happy to support these and of course take the donations.</li>
			<li>All monies raised in the UK will be donated to the Dollar Charity Committee and then divided between our approved Charities (Helen & Douglas House etc.) and all monies raised by Sii will be donated to Hospice Foundation in Gdansk.</li>
			<li>We expect all people involved to look after the bikes provided and act responsibly during the event.</li>
			<li>On completion we will auction the Exercise Bikes at an open bid event and any monies made will be added to the total. </li>
		</ul>
